## Constructor Injection in Spring

---

### 🧠 Concept First

In **Constructor Injection**, Spring injects dependencies **at the time of object creation** itself — through the constructor. No separate setter call needed.

```
Setter Injection:
1. Student s = new Student();     // object created first
2. s.setAge(21);                  // then values injected

Constructor Injection:
1. Student s = new Student(21);   // object created + values injected together
```

---

### 📌 When to Use Which

| Situation | Use |
|---|---|
| Mandatory dependencies | ✅ Constructor Injection |
| Optional dependencies | Setter Injection |
| Immutable fields (`final`) | ✅ Constructor Injection only |
| Many optional config fields | Setter Injection |
| Spring Boot best practice | ✅ Constructor Injection |

---

### ✅ Full Code

#### 📄 Address.java
```java
package com.example;

public class Address {

    private String city;
    private String state;

    // Constructor
    public Address(String city, String state) {
        this.city  = city;
        this.state = state;
    }

    public void show() {
        System.out.println("City: " + city + ", State: " + state);
    }
}
```

---

#### 📄 Student.java
```java
package com.example;

public class Student {

    private final String name;    // final → only constructor injection works
    private final int age;
    private final Address address;

    // Constructor — Spring calls this with injected values
    public Student(String name, int age, Address address) {
        this.name    = name;
        this.age     = age;
        this.address = address;
        System.out.println("Student constructor called");
    }

    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name + ", Age: " + age);
        address.show();
    }
}
```

---

#### 📄 beans.xml
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<beans xmlns="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans"
       xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
       xsi:schemaLocation="
         http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans
         http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans/spring-beans.xsd">

    <!-- Address bean — also uses constructor injection -->
    <bean id="address" class="com.example.Address">
        <constructor-arg value="Sathyamangalam"/>
        <constructor-arg value="Tamil Nadu"/>
    </bean>

    <!-- Student bean — constructor injection -->
    <bean id="student" class="com.example.Student">
        <constructor-arg value="Nivas"/>
        <constructor-arg value="21"/>
        <constructor-arg ref="address"/>  <!-- object injection -->
    </bean>

</beans>
```

> `<constructor-arg>` maps to constructor parameters **in order** (top to bottom = left to right in constructor)

---

#### 📄 App.java
```java
package com.example;

import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;
import org.springframework.context.support.ClassPathXmlApplicationContext;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        ApplicationContext ctx =
            new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext("beans.xml");

        Student s = (Student) ctx.getBean("student");
        s.show();
    }
}
```

#### 🖥️ Output
```
Student constructor called
Name: Nivas, Age: 21
City: Sathyamangalam, State: Tamil Nadu
```

